Synopsis:
   theme [theme]
   theme -save [name]

Description:
   Attempts to change the current theme to <theme>.

   If <theme> is not specified the user will be prompted to choose one from
   the list of available themes. Either name or number is accepted.

   If the -SAVE	option is present then the current settings will be written
   to the user directory as a theme named [name] (or 'custom' if none).

See Also:
   ds:dset(1);  ds:fset(1);  ds:status(1);

